text:
Ok we’re at the LBJ ranch here just outside
of Austin, Texas and we are going to go and

watch them brand the horns of the cows that’s
how they do it here let’s go take a look!

The horn is kind of like a covering and that
horn wall is about that thick probably and

inside there is stuff that looks just like
bone and in that ‘boney’ looking material

is blood vessels, nerves but as long as we
stay just in this outside wall, we’re good.

If it was hurting, she’d probably be jumping
and growling acting all different.
Do you have to press hard?

And for more great videos don’t forget to
subscribe to our channel!
